         <abstract>
            <p>An elementary method for solving simultaneous Diophantine equations is given. This method will in general lead quickly to a solution-free region on the order of $1 &lt; x &lt; 10^{10^{50}}$. The method is illustrated by applying it to a set of Diophantine equations.</p>
